caption.text:
I was watching some photography videos on youtube last night and SNAP I had a style preference shift. I began to see the beauty, if you will, of smooth, low contrast and low clarity in pictures. You can see from my previous pictures how I wasn't shy on cranking up my clarity and contrast, which isn't bad; there's really no good or bad in pictures it's just personal preferences. And who knows maybe later I'll go back to sharp "intimidating" high-contrast pictures, maybe even right after this post! But for the time being, it's smooth and low-contrast for me.
PS: Video of this photo hunting session coming soon!

If any of you lacks wisdom, you should ask God, who gives generously to all without finding fault, and it will be given to you.
James 1:5 NIV

Even though Solomon was king, he knew he was just a young helpless person who had no idea to govern a great multitude of people. So when God gave him a wish, he asked for wisdom. With the wisdom given to him, his reign became the golden age of the kingdom. Not only wisdom and knowledge of governing, Solomon also spoke proverbs, songs, biology, and other knowledge.

Sometimes we feel like we cannot do it. We have a hard time coming up with a great design, calculating complex maths, leading a group of people, raising up kids, making a thesis, speaking, writing, coding, marketing, or any kind of area in life. But like Solomon, humble yourself and ask God for wisdom, and he will give it to you and work through you.

In the end of Solomon’s life, he did not use his wisdom and he fell. Use God’s wisdom as your lifestyle in every aspect of your life until the end. When we have that wisdom, it is up to us whether to use it and act upon it or just to let it be mere knowledge.

caption.text:
We are in a process

Of becoming more to the image and likeness of God, and achieving the fullest of each of us according to his plans, for his eternal glory. I believe every agony and hardship that we encounter is part of that process. God is gracious in his gifts, but he also uses troubling situations and circumstances to train us, to mold us, and to push us further forward.

As a body builder who wouldn't earn his well-built shape if not through the painful exercises.
As a mother who wouldn't have her beautiful living child if not through the excruciating child labor process.
As an oyster that wouldn't produce a beautiful pearl if not through the wounds created by parasites and the agonizing healing system.

More pain, more glory.
More scars, more story.
More hardships we go through, more reasons to stand strong and carry on.
"The most painful part of our process will also produce the most power in our lives."
Don't give up, God's strength will keep us going

In the worst of us, that's when the best of God comes in and work.

But he (God) said to me, “My grace is sufficient for you, for my power is made perfect in weakness.” Therefore I will boast all the more gladly about my weaknesses, so that Christ’s power may rest on me. That is why, for Christ’s sake, I delight in weaknesses, in insults, in hardships, in persecutions, in difficulties. For when I am weak, then I am strong.

2 Corinthians 12:9‭-‬10 NIV
